        public void setOpticsPrimary​(java.lang.String opticsPrimary)
        Setting the primary optics that is used in the science plan. There are two types of primary optics:
        • "GNZ" for the GN Zemax Model
        • "GSZ" for the GS Zemax Model
        Parameters:
        opticsPrimary - The string to represent the primary optics (either "GNZ" or "GSZ").

      • getfStop

        public double getfStop()

      • setfStop

        public void setfStop​(double fStop)
        Setting the f-stop of the primary optics.
        • The value range of f-stop for GNZ is 1.8 - 8.1
        • The value range of f-stop for GSZ is 2.9 - 18.

      • getOpticsSecondaryRMS

        public double getOpticsSecondaryRMS()

        public void setOpticsSecondaryRMS​(double opticsSecondaryRMS)
        Setting the secondary optics that is used in the science plan, which depends on the location of the telescope.
        • South telescope (Cerro Pach√≥n, Chile): 5-13 nm
        • North telescope (Mauna Kea, Hawaii): 5-17 nm
        Parameters:
        opticsSecondaryRMS - Double value of the secondary optics within the predefined range.

        public void setScienceFoldMirrorDegree​(double scienceFoldMirrorDegree)

        Parameters:
        scienceFoldMirrorDegree - The degree value of the fold mirror degree.

        Set the type of the fold mirror. There are two options: Reflective converging beam or Cassegrain focus
        Parameters:

      • getModuleContent

        public int getModuleContent()

      • setModuleContent

        public void setModuleContent​(int moduleContent)
        There are 4 types of module content:
        • 1: Module 1 acquisition camera/high resolution wavefront sensor.
        • 2: Module 2: science fold.
        • 3: Module 3: second peripheral wavefront sensor.
        • 4: Module 4: (closest to the sky) first peripheral wavefront sensor.
        Parameters:
        moduleContent - The value of 1, 2, 3 or 4.

        • Argon

        • ThAr

        Parameters:
